		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Jan 30th 10:07 AM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=9808490714680&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=9808490714680&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=9808490714680"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9808490714680></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1721"><span id=Scholar>Dalcais</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>46 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Dalcais&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I read an interesting post on another board and tried the tactic described therein. It may be old and many of you may know of it, yet it seems underutilized and detrimental if not done occasionally. Pocupining.<br><br>When was the last time you noticed saw "You have become better at defense" or "You have become better at offense"? Most likely its been awhile if you you the more popular solo techniqes such as DD kiting and root/DoT. These skills may not seem all to important in your druidic lifestyle but I am sure there will be a day when a few points in defense or your weapon&nbsp;&nbsp;skill will save your hide, and maybe someone else's.<br><br>According to the post I read 1 point of defense is roughly the equivalent of 3 AC. I dont know how much truths in that statement but if it was a 1 defense to 1 AC ratio it would be wrth having. Another thing you might need to work on using this tactic is increasing your 1hs skill. You may be thinking, "Why!? All the really nice weapons are 1hb!" but think again friend, the druid epic weapon is a scimitar. A scimitar with huge stat increases and procs a 63% movement snare 1600 point DoT...all completely mana free.<br><br>Okay, enough of trying to convince you to use this method. I'll get down to explaining the how to...<br><br>Cast all your your best buff that are useful in combat upon yourself. At my current lvl of 29 i cast my  age old strength spell, firefist, wolf form, skin like steel, and bramblecoat. <br><br>Med to full and go find a blue con, preferably an animal. Snare and stack all DoTs available onto it. Cast your best damage sheild on yourself and melee. If your get low on health either cast panic or terrorize animal if applicable, or root it and back off to DD or DoT it down.<br><br>If needed cast treeform to regenerate hit points quickly, rinse, repeat.<br><br>At 29 I can take out 2 low blue sabertooth grimilkin in Lake of Ill Omen before i need to stop and meditate, but then again I have a pretty high wisdom, and this method might be suicide in the wrong circumstances. Be careful when first trying it out. <br><br>Live long and level, <br><br>Dalcais of Druzzil Ro</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
