		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=19949"><span id=>yuiop</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>87 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.45]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=yuiop&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>excellent idea but here is another. do the same thing as dalcais said to start but in stead dont ever kil the mob. just get its hitpoints down low to were it wants to run then snare it so it cant move(not root) then whip out that scimmy and beat it, to within an inch of its life then med till it turns and attacks you again then start beating it down again. you dont get any exp this way but it is the fastest way to increase your weapons skills and defence skills relatively safely and cost very little mana to keep the monster ensnared after the initial asault.&nbsp;&nbsp;by sitting and medding and letting the monster heal up a bit you could do this all day long on the same monster and max out your combat skills with very little risk. i always keep them maxed at every lvl 1hb 1hs off, and def.  as long as you never let them lag behind your training time will always be short but in the long run if you agro a mob off a tank you'll be at peace knowing you can take it for just a little bit longer</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Yuiop Lilcheeks<br>halfling druid&nbsp;&nbsp;on the server that rhymes with a box of rox</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
